    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "equipment",
        "text": "This arrow splits at the far end of the shaft into five branching arrowheads, making it impractical for single targets but deadly in combat. When you fire an activated *enfilading arrow*, it sails upward and shatters into countless copies. The arrows then rain down in a 10-foot burst at any point within your weapon's first range increment, dealing 6d8 piercing damage to all creatures in the area (DC 25 basic Reflex).  \n   \n If a creature critically fails the save and you have access to the bow critical specialization effect, the target is immobilized and must spend an Interact action to attempt a DC 10 Athletics check to pull the missile free; it can't move from its space until it succeeds.",
        "level": 9,
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Uncommon",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 159,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 11,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "f31704572455b8d77a8bd97c0045fde6",
                "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 26
                    }
                ],
                "schema_version": 1.1,
                "classes": [
                    "uncommon"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Conjuration",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "legacy",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Core Rulebook",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 630",
                            "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 630",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 1
                        },
                        "page": 630,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "4.0",
                            "alt": "4.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 1
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "9011037bb4a11ca6cf2d16fa8a657bf5",
                "text": "Effects and magic items with this trait are associated with the conjuration school of magic, typically involving summoning, creation, teleportation, or moving things from place to place.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "summoning",
